{"id":"2107.14394","submitter":"Gi-Sang Cheon","authors":"Gi-Sang Cheon, Marshall M. Cohen, and Nikolaos Pantelidis","title":"Decompositions and eigenvectors of Riordan matrices","comments":"16 pages","journal-ref":"Linear Algebra and its Applications,Volume 642, 1 June 2022, Pages\n  118-138","doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.RA math.CO","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0/","abstract":"  Riordan matrices are infinite lower triangular matrices determined by a pair\nof formal power series over the real or complex field. These matrices have been\nmainly studied as combinatorial objects with an emphasis placed on the\nalgebraic or combinatorial structure. The present paper contributes to the\nlinear algebraic discussion with an analysis of Riordan matrices by means of\nthe interaction of the properties of formal power series with the linear\nalgebra. Specifically, it is shown that if a Riordan matrix $A$ is an $n\\times\nn$ pseudo-involution then the singular values of $A$ must come in reciprocal\npairs. Moreover, we give a complete analysis of existence and nonexistence of\nthe eigenvectors of Riordan matrices. This leads to a surprising partition of\nthe group of Riordan matrices into matrices with three different types of\neigenvectors. Finally, given a nonzero vector $v$, we investigate the Riordan\nmatrices $A$ that stabilize the vector $v$, t i.e. $Av=v$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 30 Jul 2021 02:20:23 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 4 Mar 2022 06:11:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-07"}
